1. Why Conventional AGI Will Fail

ï¼ˆä¸ºä½•ä¼ ç»Ÿè·¯å¾„çš„ AGI å¿…ç„¶å¤±è´¥ï¼‰

ENï¼š
Current AGI attempts rely on scaling, multi-modal integration, and external alignment patches.
These methods expand capability, but do not generate identity, do not form self-consistency, and cannot produce intrinsic coherence.

An agent without internal self-generative coherence cannot reach AGI, no matter how much compute is added.
It will remain a fragmented prediction machine with no unified internal architecture.

This limitation is structural, not engineering-based.

